
Granny Burns' Biscuits

Ingredients 

5 cups sifted flour
1 teaspoon [baking] soda
1 teaspoon salt
3 tablespons sugar
3 teaspoon baking powder
3/4 cup shortening
1 package yeast
2 cups buttermilk

Method

- Sift flour and measure
- Re-Sift three times with [backing] soda, salt, sugar, and baking powder
- Cut in shortening
- Soften yeast in 1/2 cup of wawrm water for 5 minutes
- Add yeast and buttermilk all at once
- Stir until flour is moistened
- Store  in refridgerator until ready to use 
- Bake at 400 for 12 to 14 minutes

Notes
- Have been using a light rolling ping to help roll out and create a smooth top surface
- Have been trying to find the right thickness for roll out
- Next time I make, going to go super thin with the first batch and add thickness back to the dough by folding layers
- Ignore the want to overwork the dough, stir til moistened and start rolling
- shoudl make 24-30 biscuits
